Process called "apply_post_query_filters" that takes entries as List[AuditEntry] and query as AuditQuery returns List[AuditEntry]:
    Let filtered_entries be entries If query.limit is not None:
    Let start_index be if query.offset is not None then query.offset else 0
    Let end_index be Math.min with values as list containing (start_index query.limit), Collections.List.length with lst as entries
    Set filtered_entries to Collections.List.slice with lst as entries and start as start_index and end as end_index Return filtered_entries

Process called "generate_query_hash" that takes query as AuditQuery returns String:
    Let query_string be serialize_query_to_string with query as query
    Return Hash.sha256 with data as query_string

Process called "serialize_query_to_string" that takes query as AuditQuery returns String:
    Return String.concat with parts as list containing
    if query.start_time is not None then DateTime.to_iso_string with datetime as query.start_time else "",
    if query.end_time is not None then DateTime.to_iso_string with datetime as query.end_time else "",
    if query.limit is not None then String.from_int with value as query.limit else ""

Process called "analyze_compliance" that takes entries as List[AuditEntry] and regulation as String returns ComplianceData:
    Return ComplianceData with entries as entries and regulation as regulation

